# Offer of Internship — AI Intern

Date: [Date]

Dear [Candidate Name],

We are pleased to offer you an internship with Omninuera for the position of AI Intern on a fixed-term basis. This letter outlines the key terms and conditions of the internship. Please review the details and, if acceptable, sign and return a copy to indicate your acceptance.

## 1. Position and Duration
- Role: AI Intern.
- Duration: 3 months (fixed-term internship).
- Start date: [to be agreed].
- Location / Official workplace: Bengaluru (candidate is located in Bengaluru).
- Work arrangement: Fully remote.

## 2. Reporting
- Reporting to: [Hiring Manager].

## 3. Stipend and Payment
- Stipend: INR 10,000 per month.
- Payment schedule: Payable monthly in arrears, subject to standard payroll processing and any required tax deductions.
- Any statutory deductions or withholding (e.g., Tax Deducted at Source) will be applied as required by law.

## 4. Working Hours and Remote Work Expectations
- Expected hours: Approximately 40 hours per week (or as otherwise agreed with your reporting manager).
- Remote work expectations:
  - Maintain regular availability during mutually agreed core hours.
  - Attend scheduled virtual meetings, stand-ups, and training sessions.
  - Ensure a reliable internet connection and a suitable workspace to perform duties.
  - Follow Omninuera’s remote work policies and information security guidelines.

## 5. Conditions of Offer
This offer is subject to:
- Satisfactory completion of background verification checks (education, identity, and other checks as required).
- Verification of your eligibility to undertake the internship and to work remotely as required.
- Your agreement to and compliance with Omninuera policies, including confidentiality, acceptable use, and any internship-specific policies.

## 6. Intellectual Property and Confidentiality
- Intellectual Property (IP):
  - You agree that all inventions, designs, developments, discoveries, ideas, improvements, works of authorship, software code, data models, documentation, or other work product (collectively “Work Product”) developed by you, either alone or jointly with others, during the internship and within the scope of your role, shall be the sole and exclusive property of Omninuera.
  - You hereby assign and agree to assign to Omninuera all right, title, and interest in and to such Work Product and any intellectual property rights therein.
  - You agree to execute any documents and take any actions reasonably requested by Omninuera to effect or confirm such assignment.
- Confidentiality / NDA:
  - During your internship and thereafter, you shall hold in strict confidence and not disclose or use for any purpose other than performing your internship duties any confidential information of Omninuera, including but not limited to technical data, trade secrets, algorithms, business plans, customer information, pricing models, internal processes, and any other information designated as confidential.
  - You may be required to sign a separate Confidentiality Agreement or Internship NDA as a condition of this offer.

## 7. Employment Status and Benefits
- This internship is a fixed-term internship and does not constitute an offer of regular employment.
- You will not be an employee for the purposes of benefits such as health insurance, paid leave, provident fund, employee state insurance (ESI), or other employee benefits, unless otherwise required by applicable law or expressly agreed in writing.
- Omninuera will comply with legally required obligations applicable to internships under Indian law; please consult Legal for details.

## 8. Termination and Proration
- Either party may terminate the internship for any reason by providing written notice to the other party. The standard notice period is [one week] unless otherwise agreed.
- Omninuera reserves the right to terminate the internship immediately for cause (including breach of policies, misconduct, or violation of confidentiality obligations).
- If termination occurs before the end of a calendar month, the stipend for that month may be prorated on a pro rata basis for the days worked.

## 9. Data Protection and Remote Work
- While working remotely, you must adhere to Omninuera’s data protection, security, and remote access policies to safeguard company data and systems.
- Use only company-approved tools and follow instructions from IT/security teams for access to systems.

## 10. Background Checks and Privacy
- By accepting this offer, you consent to background checks described above. Background check information will be handled in accordance with applicable privacy laws and Omninuera’s privacy policies.

## 11. Miscellaneous
- This offer letter constitutes the primary terms of the internship. Additional policies, onboarding forms, and agreements (including a separate internship agreement or NDA) may be required.
- This letter does not create any obligation for Omninuera to employ you beyond the fixed-term internship period.

If you agree with the terms above, please sign below and return a scanned copy of this letter by [date or timeframe].

Sincerely,

[Authorized Representative Name]  
[Title]  
Omninuera

Acceptance — Candidate

